\label{c:invariance} 
Let $P$ be $A^*${\hyp}hyperdefinable and $V\subseteq P$. Then, $V$ is $A^*${\hyp}invariant if and only if it is setwise invariant under the action of $\Aut(\mathfrak{M}/A^*)$ on $P$, if and only if $\quot^{-1}[V]$ is $A^*${\hyp}invariant.
\begin{proof} Obvious by \cref{l:types of hyperimaginaries}. %Suppose $V$ is $A^*${\hyp}invariant and $a^*\in \quot^{-1}[V]$. Then, $\tp(a^*/A^*)\subseteq \quot^{-1}[\tp(a/A^*)]\subseteq\quot^{-1}[V]$, so $\quot^{-1}[V]$ is $A^*${\hyp}invariant. Suppose $\quot^{-1}[V]$ is $A^*${\hyp}invariant and $a\in V$. Then, $\tp(a/A^*)=\quot[\tp(a^*/A^*)]\subseteq \quot[\quot^{-1}[V]]=V$.
\end{proof}

