\label{p:product of locally hyperdefinable sets}
Let $P$ and $Q$ be locally hyperdefinable sets with global logic topologies. Then, $P\times Q$ is a locally hyperdefinable set and its product topology is its global logic topology.
\begin{proof} It suffices to note that, for any two topological spaces $X$ and $Y$ with respective local coverings $\mathcal{C}$ and $\mathcal{D}$, $\mathcal{C}\times \mathcal{D}\coloneqq \{P\times Q\sth P\in\mathcal{C},\ Q\in\mathcal{D}\}$ is a local covering of the product topology. 
\end{proof}

