semantic_equivalence_artifact.original_latex_theorem:
[Gleason{\hyp}Yamabe] \label{t:gleason yamabe} 
Let $G$ be a locally compact topological group and $U\subseteq G$ a neighbourhood of the identity. Then, $G$ has a Yamabe pair $(K,H)$ with $K\subseteq U$. In particular, a topological group has a Lie core if and only if it is locally compact.
\begin{proof} The original papers are \cite{gleason1952groups,montgomery1952small,yamabe1953conjecture,yamabe1953generalization}. A complete proofs can also be found in \cite{montgomery1955topological,tao2014hilbert}. Model{\hyp}theoretic treatments can be found in \cite{hirschfeld1990nonstandard,van2015hilbert}. 
\end{proof}

