[Gleason{\hyp}Yamabe{\hyp}Kreitlon Theorem]  \label{t:gleason yamabe carolino}
There are functions $c:\ \N\rightarrow \N$ and $d:\ \N\rightarrow\N$ such that the following holds: 

Let $G$ be a locally compact topological group and $U\subseteq G$ an open precompact $k${\hyp}approximate subgroup for some $k\in\N$. Then, $G$ has a Yamabe pair $(K,H)$ with $K\subseteq U^4$ such that $\def\rf@num{H}\def\rf@den{K}\mathpalette\rfr@c\relax$ is a Lie group of dimension at most $d(k)$ and $H\cap U^4$ generates $H$ and is $c(k)${\hyp}commensurable to $U$.

