\label{l:maximal compact normal subgroup}
Every connected Lie group has a unique maximal compact normal subgroup.  
\begin{proof} By Cartan{\hyp}Iwasawa{\hyp}Malcev Theorem \cite[Chapter XV Theorem 3.1]{hochschild1965structure}, there is a maximal compact subgroup $T$, and every compact subgroup is contained in a conjugate of it. Hence, $\bigcap_{g\in G} gTg^{-1}$ is the unique maximal compact normal subgroup. 
\end{proof}

