\label{t:canonical representation of the minimal lie core} Let $G$ be a piecewise $A${\hyp}hyperdefinable group with a generic piece. Let $L$ be the minimal $A${\hyp}Lie core of $G$ and $\pi_{L\mid G^0_A}:\ G^0_A\rightarrow L$ the restriction to $G^0_A$ of the global minimal Lie core map of $L$. Then, $G^0_A\cap G^{\mathrm{ap}}=\ker(\pi_{L\mid G^0_A})$. In particular, $L\cong\def\rf@num{G^0_A}\def\rf@den{G^{\mathrm{ap}}}\mathpalette\rfr@c\relax$. 
\begin{proof} By \cref{l:minimal yamabe pair and aperiodic component}, we know that $G^{\mathrm{ap}}\cap G^0_A\leq \ker(\pi_{L\mid G^0_A})$. On the other hand, $\ker(\pi_{L\mid G^0_A})=G^0_A\cap \pi_L^{-1}(1)\trianglelefteq G$ is $\bigwedge${\hyp}definable modulo $G^{00}_A\leq G^{\mathrm{ap}}$. Therefore, $\def\rf@num{\ker(\pi_{L\mid G^0_A})}\def\rf@den{G^{\mathrm{ap}}}\mathpalette\rfr@c\relax$ is a compact normal subgroup of $\def\rf@num{G}\def\rf@den{G^{\mathrm{ap}}}\mathpalette\rfr@c\relax$. As it is aperiodic, we conclude that $\ker(\pi_{L\mid G^0_A})\leq G^{\mathrm{ap}}$, so $\ker(\pi_{L\mid G^0_A})=G^{\mathrm{ap}}\cap G^0_A$. 
\end{proof}

