\label{c:indiscernible hyperimaginaries} 
Let $P=\prod_{t\in T}P_t$ be a product of $A${\hyp}hyperdefinable sets and $(I,<)$ an infinite linear order, with $|T|^+ +|I|\leq\kappa$. Then, a sequence $(\overline{b}_i)_{i\in I}$ of hyperimaginary tuples in $P$ is $A${\hyp}indiscernible if and only if, for some set of representatives $A^*$ of $A$, there is an $A^*${\hyp}indiscernible sequence of representatives $(\overline{b}^*_i)_{i\in I}$.

Furthermore, if $(\overline{b}_i)_{i\in I}$ is $A${\hyp}indiscernible, for any set of representatives $A^*$ there is an $A^{**}${\hyp}indiscernible sequence of representatives $(\overline{b}^*_i)_{i\in I}$ of $(\overline{b}_i)_{i\in I}$ where $A^{**}$ is another set of representatives of $A$ with $\tp(A^*)=\tp(A^{**})$. 
\begin{proof} By the Standard \cref{l:standard lemma for hyperimaginaries,c:types over hyperimaginaries}. 
\end{proof}

